MAHONING CREEK HYDROELECTRIC COMPANY, LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Mahoning Creek Hydroelectric Company, LLC ("Mahoning Creek Hydroelectric") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from a hydroelectric generation facility located in Armstrong County, Pennsylvania ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Mahoning Creek Hydroelectric's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by FERC.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total annual revenue requirement is $33,595.01. The total monthly revenue requirement is $33,595.01 / 12 = $2,799.58.
